%S A397124 1,6,84,184,8,24,304,48,4,8,16,42,8,20,16,4,8,32
%N A397124 Number of placements of n queens on distinct squares of an n X n board that leave the maximum number of unattacked vacant squares, with rotations and reflections counted as distinct.
%H A397124 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="https://github.com/manman4/OEIS_00/blob/main/019/019317/019317_01.c">C program</a> (github)
%F A397124 Under rotations and reflections of the board, the optimal n-queen placements split into equivalence classes. Let o_s(n) denote the number of these classes containing exactly s placements, where s is 1, 2, 4, or 8.
%F A397124 A019317(n) = o_1(n) +   o_2(n) +   o_4(n) +   o_8(n),
%F A397124       a(n) = o_1(n) + 2*o_2(n) + 4*o_4(n) + 8*o_8(n).
%e A397124    n  A019317(n)   (o_1,o_2,o_4,o_8)      a(n)
%e A397124 ----------------------------------------------
%e A397124    1           1          (1,0,0, 0)         1
%e A397124    2           2          (0,1,1, 0)         6
%e A397124    3          16          (0,2,8, 6)        84
%e A397124    4          25          (0,0,4,21)       184
%e A397124    5           1          (0,0,0, 1)         8
%e A397124    6           3          (0,0,0, 3)        24
%e A397124    7          38          (0,0,0,38)       304
